categories: Category:Jedi trainees of the Jedi Order

nodes.text: Wollwi Enan was a female individual from the planet of Berchest who lived in the last decades of the Galactic Republic. At an early age, she was discovered to be Force-sensitive by the Jedi Order and taken to the Jedi Temple of the planet Coruscant for training. In 26 BBY, Enan participated in the Temple's annual lightsaber tournament as part of the Apprentice Trials. During that competition, she dueled and bested her fellow Jedi youngling Telloti Cillmam'n.

Wollwi Enan was first mentioned in Hammer, a short story written by Edward M. Erdelac for the 147th issue of the Star Wars Insider magazine. "Wollwi Enan" is an anagram of "Willow Anne," which is the name of Erdelac's daughter.
